## 2. Phase B: Programmable Money (The Representative Vault)

Once the WILL NFT is mature and delegated, and the threshold is met, the system **mints** tokens. However, this money is "locked" in a logic-gated contract.

| Feature | Logic Implementation |
| --- | --- |
| **Whitelisted Spending** | Funds can only be sent to "Service Provider" addresses that have been verified or voted in as "Constructors." |
| **Milestone Vesting** | Instead of receiving 100% of the funds, the Representative contract releases 10% per milestone. |
| **The "Kill Switch"** | If 15% of the original delegators "undelegate" their WILL, the minting stops immediately and remaining funds are returned to the treasury/burned. |
| **Category Brakes** | Code prevents more than amount of money from being minted for "Social Welfare" vs "Infrastructure" in a single cycle to prevent populist inflation. |

